<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Wary" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Wary,</orth> cautious, carefully watching: <cit><quote>I have ta'en a due and w. note,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 1, 38</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>it behoves men to be w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 257</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.97" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.290" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 290</bibl> (<emph>bear a w. eye,</emph> == be attentive). <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.420" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 420</bibl>. With <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>be of thyself so w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 22.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 22, 9</bibl></cit> (== take cautious care of thyself).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>